CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F366A1771952662
OL,3,CKillamarsh killer handed another life
OL,4,Csentence for prison hammer attack
OL,6,FBendall's first blow was to the back
OL,7,Fof his head, causing Mr Mullaney to
OL,8,Fslump unconscious to the floor before
OL,9,Fhe was hit three more times, the court
OL,10,Fheard.
OL,12,FHe had also used a claw hammer to
OL,13,Fconduct the horrific killings in
OL,14,FKillamarsh, Derbyshire, in 2021.
OL,16,FThe attack in a workshop in May 2024
OL,17,Fwas so severe that a prison officer
OL,18,Fbelieved the victim could be dead,
OL,19,FJolyon Perks, prosecuting, said.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G2/8
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,367,360,260,120,000,100
PN,36603
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F366A1771952662
OL,3,CKillamarsh killer handed another life
OL,4,Csentence for prison hammer attack
OL,6,FWhen the officer drew his baton and
OL,7,Fsounded an alarm, Bendall submitted,
OL,8,Fthe court heard.
OL,10,FMr Perks said: "The defendant
OL,11,Fimmediately threw his hammer to one
OL,12,Fside and put his arms out to show he
OL,13,Fhad stopped his assault on Mr
OL,14,FMullaney."
OL,16,FAfter he was handcuffed, officers
OL,17,Fasked Bendall why he had attacked his
OL,18,Ffriend, with whom he had sometimes
OL,19,Fplayed dominos.
OL,26,@rD@POUvD@JO]
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G3/8
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,367,360,260,120,000,100
PN,36604
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F366A1771952662
OL,3,CKillamarsh killer handed another life
OL,4,Csentence for prison hammer attack
OL,6,FMr Perks said: "The defendant
OL,7,Fresponded 'I don't know'."
OL,9,FHis victim spent four nights in the
OL,10,FRoyal Victoria Infirmary, Newcastle,
OL,11,Fbeing treated for depressed skull
OL,12,Ffractures and bleeding on the brain.
OL,14,FThe court heard that the severity to
OL,15,Fthe blows could have been fatal.
OL,17,FIn a victim statement made three
OL,18,Fmonths after the attack, Mr Mullaney
OL,19,Fsaid it had left him anxious,
OL,20,Freluctant to leave his cell and
OL,21,Fstruggling to sleep.
OL,26,@nD@POUoD@ZO]
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G4/8
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
